16/03/2004
BAKU, Azerbaijan -- The Turkish Defence Ministry launched a NATO-sponsored security course in Azerbaijan on Monday (15 March). 
General Omer Bayrakli, military attach√© at the Turkish Embassy in Azerbaijan, said NATO participation in the resolution of the Nagorno-Karabakh conflict between Azerbaijan and Armenia was in Azerbaijan's interest.
In other news, police in Istanbul announced on Monday that they seized a total of 153.8kg of heroin in two separate operations. 
In both cases, the heroin was allegedly smuggled from Afghanistan and Iran and destined for Europe. 
(Anadolu Agency, Trend, TRT - 15/03/04)
